{
  "texts": [
    "They leverage dynamic graph embeddings to capture both the topology and its temporal changes.",
    "DynGEM [64], for instance, employs an autoencoder to learn the embeddings from each snapshot of the DTDG.",
    "Interestingly, the autoencoder at time initializes its parameters based on the autoencoder from time.",
    "The architecture of this autoencoder, including the number of layers and neurons in each layer, is adjusted based on the differences between the current snapshot and its predecessor.",
    "The Net2Net [65] technique is utilized to maintain the mapping relationships across layers when modifications are made to the autoencoder."
  ]
}